Recently, there have been a number of excellent libraries to facilitate standard implementations of numerous recommendation algorithms and tasks.
These libraries significantly contribute to the reproducibility of the recommendation research community.
For instance,
BARS <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_citep">(Zhu et&#160;al<span class="ltx_text">.</span>, <a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2405.18058v1#bib.bib72" title="">2022</a>)</cite>, including BART-CTR and BARS-Batch, targets open benchmarks for both CTR prediction and candidate item matching tasks on a variety of public datasets.
RecBole&#160;
(Zhu et al., 2022), including BART-CTR and BARS-Batch, targets open benchmarks for both CTR prediction and candidate item matching tasks on a variety of public datasets.
